        "v5": {
            "text": "Who amasses wealth and counts it over and over.[c]<i> </i>[4836]",
            "notes": [
                {
                    "ref": "c",
                    "note": "9:34; 89:21."
                },
                {
                    "ref": "4836",
                    "note": "<p><strong>Important Words:</strong></p><p>عدد (counts it over and over) is syn. with عدد (‘<i>adada</i>) and also has an intensive signification. عددہ means, he reckoned it time after time; he made it numerous; he made it a provision against the casualties of time. عددت المیت means, I enumerated the good qualities of the dead person (Lane &amp; Aqrab).</p><p>مالا (wealth) means, great wealth; small wealth; worthless wealth which is great in the eyes of him who amasses it but small and worthless in the sight of God.</p><p><strong>Commentary:</strong></p><p>The verse constitutes a sad commentary on man’s passion for worldly riches. Worship of Mammon is the bane of the materialistic civilization of the day.</p>"
                }
